This place used to be my go to for lunch. The sandwiches were always fresh and delish. The last 3 times have not been so great. Ive ordered simple things like a chicken sandwich and got a fish filet or a ham and cheese with lettuce and mayo and got ham and cheese with only tomatoe. I wanted to give them one last chance before fully throwing in the towel. I ordered my sandwich (ham and cheese w/ lettuce and mayo) at 11:23. People were coming and going, and they ordered hot food items. I waited until 11:50 to ask for my money back. I know, insane to wait that long for a sandwich, but i was seriously craving it. The woman checked and my sandwich was ready. She asked if I still wanted it and of course I did (literally waited 30 minutes for a cold cut sandwich, wasting my entire lunch break). The wrapping was piping hot. So naturally, I checked it. Sure enough, it was entirely the wrong thing. Grilled cheese sandwich with ham. This saddened me. The family that owns this place are incredibly nice. But everything else has fallen to the waistside in recent months. I angrily threw out my rewards card, and shall never return.

If I could give negative  10 stars I would.  I ordered a Flounder's Sub Special for $9.95.  The sub was sloppy and soggy, the lettuce wilted, the fried onions were piled on the sub, weighing it down and making it impossible to eat.  The hots were not spread evenly on the sub and appeared as if they were just thrown on--the sub went in the trash.  When I called to complain, I was told by the owner to bring the "product back".  When I explained to her that I would not be able to  do that (lunch hour was over and I had thrown it away), she suggested I dig the sub from the trash and bring it back the following day!  Really?   Just so  that you don't have to refund my money or provide a well-made sub?  You are the epitome of  poor business practice, and you suck in customer service.    I will not be returning and will advise my colleagues not to service your establishment.
